4:
How many times do I have to say
the same thing? You're out of sync!
Everyone's off in their own different
world!
5:
Ugh. What else could I expect from
this boorish bunch of "adventurers"?
This level of quality would never fly
in the Farlands.
7:
Oh, my apologies, your imperial
highness. Unlike you Farlandian tree
trunks, we have to MOVE while
playing.
9:
And I'll have you know, playing the
notes on the page just as they are is
considered boring in Palpebra. We
prefer to improvise here.
13:
All right everyone, let's calm down
here! And you need to tone it down,
Elsie!
16:
Marching is supposed to be fun! We
don't need to stand around and yell
at each other.
19:
Tsk... As drum major, you're
responsible for your underlings'
actions. If you knew what was best,
you'd cut this girl from the band!
21:
The drum major is the guiding star
of the entire ensemble. You need to
set a strong example for the team!
23:
Any idiot can have "fun" while
playing music. We need to aspire to
more. What is it you want this band
to accomplish, Major?
29:
If you can't answer that question,
then you clearly do not meet our
standards. Now, be quiet and follow
what we do.
35:
What you want to accomplish, huh...
That's a tough question.
40:
Yeah. I'll tell you what I really want to
do right now... I want to run away to
another world and go to one of Dia's
concerts!
44:
But you were fine with being a drum
major before this, right?
47:
Yeah. Well, there was a bit of trouble
with Elsie at this one performance
when I took over the role from my
predecessor.
50:
And, now that I think about it, she
asked me the same thing. "What do
you want to do?"
59:
I want everyone to get together,
have the time of their lives, and give
the audience a great show.
61:
That's the type of band I want to
lead. That's what I promised
everyone when I became drum
major.
64:
But part of me knows that it's not all
about just having fun...
72:
Apparently. Everyone keeps telling
me that—the Farlands girl, and
plenty of others.
77:
I don't know, that seems like a great
goal to me. If it motivates you to
keep going, then what's the problem?
81:
Really? Do you think the others
would be okay with that?
84:
Sure. They might need a little
convincing, though. You'll have to
add on a bit, no doubt, but it could
work.
88:
Convince them... Right. To get
everyone to play their best and
have fun, I have to convince them...
94:
Your world is transparent. Did you
know that?
97:
That's really the best way I can think
to phrase it—despite its lack of clear
physical manifestation, your power
still has a presence.
100:
It allows you to get close to other
people's "worlds." To support them.
103:
That's why you need to learn more
about the people you get close to.
Doing so will let you make the most
out of your power.
109:
I'm starting to get what Professor
Nicola was talking about....
112:
Hey! Do you know anyone in this city
who's familiar with music from the
Farlands?
116:
Gah. This visit is supposed to prove
our friendship, huh? What a load of
nonsense. This is all just a stunt by
those nerds from House Sextan.
120:
Excuse me, um, do you have a
moment?
123:
Huh? I mean, I guess. What do you
want?
125: I have an answer for you!
129:
It's super simple, just one word: fun! I
want to have fun with my band. No
matter what.
132:
Did we not go over this? Give a
toddler a flute and they'll be over
the moon—literally anyone can
have "fun."
138:
What I want is for everyone to have
fun: the players AND the audience! I
want them to be happy!
142:
That's my goal. That's my dream.
That's what I'll lead the band toward!
145:
...A-all right. Fine. Let me see you put
your money where your mouth is.
Show me!
148:
That's exactly what I came here to
do!
154:
Yes, but next time, give me some
advance notice before you pull a
stunt like this!
155:
Still. I think I managed to whip the
group up into shape in time.
160:
Let's get started. Remember
everyone, have FUN!
163:
I see... They're playing in a
Farlandian style.
164:
But is this really the "fun" you were
talking about?
167:
We're not done yet! The show's just
begun!
172:
I get it now. In your own way, you
guys were trying to understand us.
To adapt to our ways.
175:
But you don't need to. Be yourselves,
play like you normally would, and go
all out!
185:
Wow! That was spectacular! What a
performance...
186:
Music from the Farlands isn't half
bad, either! Go figure.
193:
Why, thank you! I feel confident in
saying that was a BIG success!
198:
Doesn't look like it did much
diplomacy-wise, though. They're still
arguing.
201:
I told you, you were marching too
fast! That's not an easy piece, and
we're still learning it! Put yourselves
in our shoes for once!
203:
Huh? We let YOU pick the pieces!
We're putting up with your stale
taste in music, so we get to perform
the piece how we want!
206:
Hahaha, don't worry about it. Those
two are always like that.
209:
And, um... thanks. If it weren't for you,
I don't think I could have pulled this
off.
212: Did that clear up your concerns?
217:
It did. Very much so. And it was all
because of your support!
